## Remarks  
 The <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticValue.Item%2A> is read-only and generates exceptions if members are modified.  

 You can only access data by key value at run-time, not at compile-time, for example to check `semantic["myKey"].Value`. Specifying a key that is not present generates an exception.  

 To detect the presence of a given key, use the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticValue.ContainsKey%2A> property on an <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticValue> instance.  



## Examples  
 The following example shows a handler for a <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.Grammar.SpeechRecognized> event designed to handle commands to change foreground and background color.  

